The paper discusses a framework for assessing the quality of Linked Open Data, which involves data management, artificial intelligence, information retrieval, software engineering, and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (databases), followed by cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.SE (software engineering), and cs.DL (machine learning).
